README

Created by Justin Wong
jkwongfl@yahoo.com

First started ~ Jan 2017
Last updated - May 5, 2017

A programming/simulation project to visualize an origami theorem. Intended for educational use.

Inspired by Erik Demaine's viedo lectures.

Known Issues:
- Saving more than once crashes
- Clicking "Cancel" in the save dialog crashes
- Clicking the top-right [X] on the save dialog crashes
- Clicking help more than once crashes
- Clicking "Make Foldable" with a blank canvas crashes; need to fix method with array to account for this case
- Clicking "Fold It!" with a blank canvas crashes; see above

Fixed Issues:
- Angles are not correct, especially around 180 degrees; need to fix math